'''''Retail Week''''' is the UKâ€™s leading news  for the  industry, covering food, fashion, property, technology and stores.
Founded in 1988 by City journalist , it is now owned by , a media company listed on the London Stock Exchange.
The magazine is published every Friday. It has an ABC-audited circulation of 10,260 and a readership of approximately 50,000.
Subscribers are primarily retail company board directors and senior managers, as well as suppliers to retailers and investment analysts.
''Retail Week'' launched a news website, in 2004. In 2007, the site was redesigned and relaunched.
''Retail Week'' has been edited since January 2005 by Tim Danaher. The previous editors were Ian McGarrigle, Kate Oppenheim and Neill Denny.